g.title: j207702174
g.text: What made you want to become a soldier?

g.title: j2426913204
g.text: What was it like growing up, you and Eleanor?

g.title: j2686637583
g.text: Yeah. Isn't that how this is supposed to work?

g.title: j3226305725
g.text: Do you think I know you well enough to jump into that?

g.title: j2955635971
g.text: Right. Stranded in an alternate dimension.

g.title: j656358664
g.text: I'm just trying to get to know you better.

g.title: j1170262733
g.text: You're less used to "people" than I am.

g.title: j1721172495
g.text: Going right into my deep personal history isn't the way to do it, mate.

g.title: j3405807244
g.text: So how am I supposed to do it?

g.title: j2309433494
g.text: Do I just stop now, or...?

g.title: j616563243
g.text: You have to buy a man a few drinks first.

g.title: j1717450085
g.text: Drinks first. *Then* personal questions. Got it.

g.title: j942160108
g.text: Not worth the trouble, never mind. [End.]

g.title: j993584402
g.text: Heh. At least you learn quick.

g.title: j3623810696
g.text: I put him in the tank, the water turned gray a minute later.

g.title: j2605977676
g.text: If it was, I'd never admit it. Luckily it isn't.

g.title: j317195626
g.text: Thought he was going to pop off.

g.title: j2778670891
g.text: On the first try, too. How'd you know?

g.title: j628887345
g.text: Let me put you out of your misery, or we'll be at this all day.

g.title: j3569745054
g.text: Did this get you what you were looking for?

g.title: j219025789
g.text: That's a *place,* not a name, you daftie!

g.title: j1054640035
g.text: I assume you fixed the water issue.

g.title: j721427586
g.text: Sure, if that's all you're willing to share.

g.title: j1708786026
g.text: Yeah, we'll call that good enough for now.

g.title: j1024321314
g.text: Black isn't even a real color, anyway. [End.]

g.title: j3226981710
g.text: I don't know that much about you two, actually.

g.title: j1166601451
g.text: The bandana you have around your skana.

g.title: j3474142131
g.text: You just "feel" like a red guy.

g.title: j76337681
g.text: Sorry I'm not up to date on my 20th-Century Britannic names!

g.title: j808089916
g.text: How was I supposed to know?

g.title: j1384263562
g.text: Yes, I fixed the damn water.

g.title: j3632452181
g.text: Couldn't be trusted with anything bigger.

g.text: Didn't figure you for the pedantic type.

g.title: j1638860733
g.text: And I'm not about to start unloading family history to you, so don't try.

g.title: j3206882109
g.text: Yeah, well. Not like I chose it.

g.title: j1716244363
g.text: I think I'm going to cry, I'm laughing so hard.

g.title: j1713834577
g.text: There's a big gap between "what's your favourite colour" and "tell me your family history."

g.title: j273553895
g.text: How'd you get that sword, anyway? It never seems to leave your side.

g.title: j2671543839
g.text: What were your lives like, before all this?

g.title: j1525956868
g.text: I take after the smart one. ;)

g.title: j2343692414
g.text: Just wasn't that kind of kid, is all.

g.title: j3496490313
g.text: There's a big gap between "what's your middle name" and "tell me your family history."

g.title: j2277361285
g.text: And with that attitude, you won't. [End.]

g.title: j1924423116
g.text: A long story for another day. After drinks. Anyway.

g.title: j1205357421
g.text: Careful, or it's going to be what I call you now.

g.title: j720301559
g.text: There's a big gap between "what was your first pet" and "tell me your family history."

g.text: It's James, by the way. And thanks for the laugh.

g.text: Something to work toward, I suppose.
